gas sample is in the { range of $1.0_{-1.0}^{+14.8}$ $\\times$10$^{-16}-\n2.5_{-2.4}^{+1.4}$ $\\times$10$^{-15}$ s$^{-1}$. This is $\\sim$2 times higher\nthan the average value measured at higher extinction, supporting an attenuation\nof CRs as suggested by theoretical models.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 25 Feb 2023 03:25:19 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 6 Apr 2023 11:43:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-07"}
